-- Central Bank Sells Three-Year Bills Unchanged at 2.65% Yield, Traders Say
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-29T02:06:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/central-bank-sells-three-year-bills-unchanged-at-2-65-yield-traders-say.html

          
          
             The Peopleâ€™s Bank of China sold
three-year bills at an unchanged yield of 2.65 percent, having
dropped 3 basis points in the previous sale, according to
traders at BOC International (China) Ltd. and China Citic Bank
Corp.  
 The monetary authority offered 85 billion yuan ($12.5
billion) of the securities at the auction today.  
 The yield dropped at five sales previously since the
central bank resumed bi-weekly offerings of the securities April
8 to help drain cash from the financial system.  
